            🔹 Picture Quality (10/10)

            The 4K Ultra HD panel with X-Reality PRO and Dolby Vision brings out deep blacks, punchy colors, and a realistic contrast. Watching nature documentaries, action movies, and even IPL matches is a visual treat. The HDR support works beautifully, especially in darker scenes.

            🔹 Sound Quality (8.5/10)

            The inbuilt 20W speakers with Dolby Audio are surprisingly good for casual viewing. Dialogue clarity is strong, and there’s decent bass for a slim TV. If you’re an audiophile or binge-watcher, consider adding a compact soundbar—but for most users, this does the job well.

            🔹 Smart Features & UI (9/10)

            Powered by Google TV, the UI is clean and fast. All major apps like Netflix, Prime Video, YouTube, and Hotstar come pre-installed and load quickly. Voice search with Google Assistant is accurate. Chromecast and Apple AirPlay 2 are also built-in—big plus for me.

            🔹 Design & Build (9.5/10)

            It looks stunning on the wall—thin bezels, premium matte finish with wall mount and a sturdy stand if you prefer table-top setup. Feels modern and minimalistic, just how I like it.

            🔹 Connectivity (9/10)

            Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, 3 HDMI ports (1 with ARC), and 2 USB ports cover all the basics. Works great with my Fire TV stick, PS5, and external hard drive.

            ⸻

            🔚 Final Verdict:

            If you’re looking for a reliable 55-inch TV with superb visuals, decent sound, and all the smart features you’d expect in 2025, this Sony Bravia model won’t disappoint. It’s perfect for both everyday TV viewing and cinematic weekend binge sessions. Slightly premium-priced, but you’re paying for quality and brand trust.
